Your Privacy Matters at Gaia!
Here's how we protect your data and respect your privacy.
General Information
The sites to which the following Privacy Notice applies are: www.gaia.com (collectively, “the Websites”). The operator of the Websites is Gaia, Inc., a Colorado corporation, 833 W. South Boulder Road, Louisville, Colorado 80027. You can reach our data protection officer at
Privacy@Gaia.com
.
Responsibilities
Our responsibility
: If you are a Gaia member, or just visiting our website, this privacy notice applies to you. If you are a registered member of Gaia we act as the ‘data controller’ of personal information about you and your use of Gaia.
Your responsibility
: Read this Privacy Notice
When and how we collect data
From the first moment you interact with Gaia, we are collecting data. Sometimes you provide us with data, sometimes we collect data about you.
Here’s when and how we collect data:
You become a Gaia member
You browse any page of our website
You use Gaia services through a device
You receive emails from us
You contact us for member support
You opt-in to or interact with our marketing messages
Types of data we collect
Identifiers
: “Identifiers” covers a broad range of information, including things like name, email address, and IP address. We collect personal information that falls into this category. For example, for subscribers we have an email address and payment information. We collect IP addresses when you connect to our service online. These sorts of identifiers are connected to your Gaia account. There are also identifiers we use for purposes like advertising (third party advertising cookies on our website) that can be used to reach you with promotional messages on other websites and applications.
Internet or other electronic network activity information
: Our service is an online service, so we collect CCPA personal information in this category, such as your interactions and activities within our service.
Geolocation data
: Our streaming application does not collect precise geolocation data from GPS sensors. However, we do collect IP addresses so we can determine your general location in order to give you a better first interaction with our service.
Inferences
: We have a recommendation system that tries to help return you custom titles based on what we feel you will like most.
Types of data we do not collect
Sensitive data
: We don’t collect any "sensitive data" about you (like racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious/philosophical beliefs, trade union membership, genetic data, biometric data, health data, data about your sexual life or orientation, and offences or alleged offences).
Children’s data
: Gaia’s website and services are not intended for or directed to users under the age of 18. We do not knowingly or intentionally collect personal information from children under the age of 13 or other minors. Where appropriate, we take reasonable measures to determine that our users are adults of legal age and to inform minors not to submit information to the Websites or the Services, or in response to advertisements.
How and why we use your data
We can only use your data for certain reasons and where we have a legal basis to do so. Here are the reasons for which we process your data:
Keeping Gaia running
: Login and authentication, processing payments.
Improving Gaia
: Testing features, managing landing pages, traffic optimization and data analysis and research.
Member Support
: Notifying you of any changes to our service, solving issues via support, including any bug fixing.
Newsletter
: Sending you emails and messages about new services, and content.
Marketing
: Identifying you as someone who might wish to buy a Gaia membership or upgrade an existing membership.
We allow others to provide analytics services and serve advertisements on our behalf across the web and in mobile applications. These entities use cookies, web beacons, device identifiers and other technologies to collect information about your use of our Website and other websites and online services, including your IP address, device identifiers, web browser, mobile network information, pages viewed, time spent on pages or in apps, links clicked, and conversion information. This information may be used by us and others to, among other things, analyze and track data, determine the popularity of certain content, deliver advertising and content targeted to your interests on our services and other websites and online services, and better understand your online activity. You can disable cookies used for advertising purposes through our cookie preferences manager. Or, for more information about interest-based ads, including to use ad industry tools to opt out of having your web browsing information used for behavioral advertising purposes, please visit
www.aboutads.info/choices
( if you are in the EU, please visit
www.youronlinechoices.eu
). Your mobile device should also include a feature that allows you to opt out of having certain information collected through apps used for behavioral advertising purposes.
Except as required by applicable law, we do not respond to or honor “do not track” (a/k/a DNT) signals or similar mechanisms automatically transmitted by web browsers for which we are cannot evaluate your choice.
Sharing of Your Information
Gaia may share your personal information, with the following:
Gaia’s parent, affiliates, subsidiaries, or successors (“Gaia Parties”).
Third parties who are under obligations of confidentiality with any of the Gaia Parties.
The following describes some of the ways that your personal information may be disclosed to third parties:
