The purposes of data processing
The categories of third parties to whom the data may be disclosed
How long the data will be stored (or the criteria used to determine that period)
Your other rights regarding our use of your data
You have the right to make us correct any inaccurate personal information about you.
You can object to us using your data for profiling you or making automated decisions about you
: We may use your data to determine whether we should let you know information that might be relevant to you (for example, tailoring emails to you based on your behavior). Otherwise, the only circumstances in which we will do this is to provide the Gaia service to you.
You have the right to be ‘forgotten’ by us and have us delete your personal information
: You can do this by asking us to erase any personal information we hold about you if it is no longer necessary for us to hold the data for purposes of your use of Gaia.
You have a right to file a complaint regarding our use of your data
: Please tell us first, so we have a chance to address your concerns. Any claims or complaints must be filed a court of competent jurisdiction in the State of Colorado, U.S.A.
We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your rights under such laws.
